# Competitor Product & Pricing Analysis – Dessert Market (Eid Campaigns)

## 📘 Overview
This project involved manual competitor analysis of premium dessert brands in Saudi Arabia, focusing on seasonal launches (especially Eid). I gathered and organized product pricing, descriptions, and launch information from public menus and promotional materials.

The purpose was to compare product positioning, price tiers, and variety across brands to inform internal product strategy.

## 🛠️ Tools Used
- Microsoft Excel (Data Structuring & Categorization)
- PDF Reporting
- Visual Analysis (Charts, Tables)

## 📊 Key Actions
- Collected and recorded 25+ SKUs weekly from 3 competitor brands  
- Grouped products into standardized categories (e.g., Cakes, Boxes, Trays)  
- Built Excel tables to compare pricing and launch frequency  
- Highlighted seasonal bundling and language trends in product names

## 💡 Key Insights
- Clear use of premium pricing strategy around seasonal products  
- Eid campaigns were heavily used for upselling via gift boxes and trays  
- Certain naming and packaging styles repeated across brands

## 📁 Files Included
- `product_launch_table.xlsx` – Full competitor product table  
- `launch_trends.pdf` – Visual summary of trends  
- `README.md` – Project description
